Step 1. Calculate Return on Equity (ROE)  
• Net Profit (from the income statement): 1,290,835.16  
• Owner’s Equity:  
 – Beginning Owner’s Equity (from the balance sheet): 28,000,000.00  
 – Ending Owner’s Equity: 29,290,835.16  
• Average Owner’s Equity = (28,000,000.00 + 29,290,835.16) / 2 ≈ 28,645,417.58  
• ROE = Net Profit / Average Owner’s Equity = 1,290,835.16 / 28,645,417.58 ≈ 0.0451, or 4.51%

Step 2. Calculate Debt to Asset Ratio  
• Total Liabilities (from the balance sheet):  
 – Given as “Total Current Liabilities” = 4,319,436.82  
• Total Assets (from the balance sheet): 33,610,271.98  
• Debt to Asset Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Assets ≈ 4,319,436.82 / 33,610,271.98 ≈ 0.1285, or about 0.13 when rounded

Step 3. Calculate Gross Profit Margin  
• Gross Profit (from the income statement): 4,788,736.33  
• Total Revenue (from the income statement): 16,388,736.33  
• Gross Profit Margin = Gross Profit / Total Revenue = 4,788,736.33 / 16,388,736.33 ≈ 0.2921, or 29.21%

Thus, the final answer is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Return on Equity (ROE)": "4.51%",
    "Debt to Asset Ratio": "0.13",
    "Gross Profit Margin": "29.21%"
  }
}
